<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AIR COMPRESSOR: MIDLAND MODELS EL-1300 AND EL-1600 - CLEAN, INSPECT AND REPAIR - CRANKSHAFT BEARING CAPS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="0">
        <title>CRANKSHAFT BEARING CAPS</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Examine crankshaft front and rear bearing caps and replace if worn or cracked.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Compressors with ball type rear bearing have a seal and spring or bowed washer in the rear
                bearing cap.
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Check the wear of the seal where it contacts the crankshaft. The seal must be replaced
                    if grooved more than 0.005 inch (.127 mm). Measure outside diameter of seal ring. If diameter is not
                    within
                    <hotlnk document="s04011_31.xml" xrefid="hl0401103">SPECIFICATIONS</hotlnk>, the seal ring must be
                    replaced.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Check the oil seal spring for loads at assembled heights. Spring must conform to
                    <hotlnk document="s04011_31.xml" xrefid="hl0401103">SPECIFICATIONS</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Some compressors have bowed washers. If washer shows wear, replace washer.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
